What is derived
---------------
The CTLL compile-time LL(1) parser (ctll::fixed_string and supporting
headers, provided by the compile-time-lark submodule) is copied from
notre, where it descends from Hana Dusikova's CTRE with modifications.
This repository began as a clone of its sibling compile-time-xml
(https://github.com/alexios-angel/compile-time-xml) and keeps its git
history; the build and packaging scaffolding follows the sibling
projects compile-time-json and compile-time-json5
(https://github.com/alexios-angel/). The HTML grammar, the
tree-construction layer, document types and the ctjs API are
original to this repository, but follow the architecture CTRE
established (compile-time tables driven by CTLL with a type-level
result).

The named character reference data (include/ctjs/entities.hpp,
generated by tools/gen-entities.py) is the WHATWG HTML Standard's
named character references table
(https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/named-characters.html),
obtained via CPython's html.entities module.

Attribution for the parser architecture and the CTLL engine belongs to
Hana Dusikova; this file preserves it as required by Section 4(c) of
the Apache License 2.0.

The grammar layer is ctlark
(https://github.com/alexios-angel/compile-time-lark), a git submodule
under external/: the HTML grammar is written in the Lark grammar
language, designed by Erez Shinan and the lark-parser project
(https://github.com/lark-parser/lark, MIT license); see ctlark's
NOTICE for the full lineage, including the Tablewright-generated
grammar-of-grammars table.
